         <gmd:abstract>
            <gco:CharacterString>Chlorophyll-a is an important pigment contained in all plants. Measurements of chlorophyll-a concentration are key to understanding the distribution and abundance of phytoplankton in the global oceans.  The product given here was produced as part of the Ocean Color Climate Change Initiative (OC-CCI) project.  The empirical NASA OC4v6 algorithm was used on water-leaving reflectances at four wavelengths.  The product is provided in units of mg Chl m-3 and at daily temporal resolution with a spatial resolution of â‰ˆ 4 km/pixel.  A global daily file will contain 4320 rows and 8640 columns of data.</gco:CharacterString>
         </gmd:abstract>
